04/03/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- US Undersecretary of State for Political Affairs Marc Grossman says Albania is moving further towards democracy. The Albanian Daily News on Friday (4 March) quoted Grossman as saying the situation regarding freedom, democracy and human rights is improving. Whiling praising the role Albania has played in the global war against terrorism, Grossman urged the government to address outstanding problems, including corruption, organised crime and human trafficking.
In other news, parliament on Thursday approved the new electoral map of the country. Following months of intense debates, the larger political parties managed to strike a compromise. The smaller parties have rejected the plan, however, saying the larger ones distributed the districts among themselves. (Albanian Daily News - 04/03/05)
